<p>i'm have a old framework here in my job, and i want to connect to ldap. I use the plugin upSimpleLdapPlugin in symfony 1.4.</p>  <p>in root/app/admin/config/app.yml </p>  <pre><code>#all:  #sf_guard_plugin:    #profile_field_name: user_id ldap:   host: 192.168.x.xxx   port: 389   user: admin   pass: xxx@xxxx   baseuser: dc=DC,dc=DC,dc=com,dc=br   version: 3 </code></pre>  <p>in apps\admin\modules\sfGuardAuth\actions\actions.class.php</p>  <pre><code> public function executeSignin($request)  {       $login = $request-&gt;getParameter('username');      $pass = $request-&gt;getParameter('password');      $user = $this-&gt;getUser();    if ($user-&gt;isAuthenticated())   {     return $this-&gt;redirect('@homepage');   }    $this-&gt;setLayout(false);     $class = sfConfig::get('app_sf_guard_plugin_signin_form','sfGuardFormSignin');     $this-&gt;form = new $class();  if ($request-&gt;isMethod('post')) {   $this-&gt;form-&gt;bind($request-&gt;getParameter('signin'));      try {            $ldap = new ldapAuth();            if($ldap-&gt;authenticate($login, $pass)){                 $user-&gt;setAuthenticated(true);                 $user-&gt;addCredential('user');                  return true;             } else{                  echo 'has an error';                  return false;             }          }      catch (Exception $e) {             echo 'erro: ',  $e-&gt;getMessage(), "\n";         } </code></pre>  <p>and i get this error:</p>  <pre><code>    Warning: ldap_bind(): Unable to bind to server: Can't contact LDAP server in ...plugins\upSimpleLdapPlugin\lib\ldapAuth.class.php on line 38 erro: Não é possível se conectar ao servidor LDAP : erro de autenticação  </code></pre>  <p>the error referes to the line 38: </p>  <pre><code>         $binded = ldap_bind($this-&gt;ds, $ldap_user, $ldap_pass); </code></pre>